# Course Details System

The Course Details screen is the **decision-making layer** between discovery and learning.

It must convert intent into enrollment.

---

# Product Vision

Course Details must:

- Clearly explain course value
- Break down learning structure
- Show progress expectations
- Preview learning outcomes
- Enable enrollment or continuation

It is both informational and motivational.

---

# Architecture

Presentation Layer

↓

CourseDetailsController (Riverpod)

↓

CourseDetailsState

↓

CoursesRepository

↓

API + Cache Layer

---

# State Management

CourseDetailsState includes:

- loading
- error
- loaded
- refreshing

Core Data:

- courseInfo
- modules
- lessonsPreview
- prerequisites
- userProgress
- AIInsights

Never use boolean flags.

---

# Course Structure Display

Must render hierarchy:

Course

→ Modules

→ Lessons

→ Topics (optional)

Each level must be collapsible.

---

# Enrollment Logic

If user is not enrolled:

- Show "Enroll" CTA

If enrolled:

- Show "Continue Learning"

AI may adjust CTA label dynamically.

---

# AI Integration

AI provides:

- Course difficulty explanation
- Readiness assessment
- Suggested starting point
- Weakness indicators

AI insights must be explainable.

---

# Navigation Rules

Course Details leads to:

- Lesson Player
- Module View
- Quiz Entry Points
- Bookmarking

Back navigation returns to:

- Courses list or Dashboard

---

# Offline Behaviour

Course structure must be cached.

Offline:

- Allow browsing
- Disable enrollment
- Allow continue learning if already enrolled

---

# API Contracts

GET /courses/{id}

GET /courses/{id}/details

GET /courses/{id}/progress

POST /courses/{id}/enroll

---

# Analytics Events

course_details_view

course_preview_expand

course_enroll_click

course_continue_click

course_ai_insight_view

---

# UI Composition Rules

Course Details must include:

Header with course title

Progress summary (if enrolled)

Module breakdown

AI insight panel

Prerequisites section

CTA section

---

# UX Rules

- Avoid information overload
- Prioritize clarity over density
- Use progressive disclosure for modules
- Keep CTA always visible on scroll

---

# Error Handling

If course fails to load:

- fallback to cached version
- show retry option
- preserve navigation integrity

---

# Performance

Course details must render shell instantly (<200ms)

Modules should lazy load.

---

# Accessibility

Must support:

- screen reader navigation
- collapsible sections accessibility labels
- proper heading hierarchy
- keyboard navigation

---

# Testing Requirements

Unit Tests:

CourseDetailsController

Module parsing logic

Enrollment logic

Widget Tests:

Course header

Module tree

AI insight panel

Integration Tests:

Course detail load

Enrollment flow

Offline browsing

---

# Cursor Instructions

When generating course detail features:

- Always include hierarchical structure rendering
- Always support AI insights panel
- Always support offline browsing
- Always include enrollment state switching
- Never flatten course structure into a single list